{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "While identity management ensures that only pre-authorized members can join the network, channels are private communication pathways in the network where the data on a channel is only available to the members of that channel, and not to the other peers in the network [7].We can program smart contracts to rely on information from the outside world such as weather information, player statistics, and fixtures results by using oracles [22].",
    "Oracles are a middleware between the blockchain and the external world that allows to fetch external data on the blockchain, however, the use of oracles brings back centralization which negates the decentralized nature of blockchain and eventually can present a single point of failure and risks bringing corrupt, or inaccurate data, which is commonly known as the oracle problem.",
    "Hence, many oracles proposals, and platforms have emerged recently to solve this problem [21,22].",
    "Provable is an oracle service utilized by numerous blockchains, including Ethereum, Hyperledger Fabric, Corda, and others.",
    "To solve the Oracle problem, Provable uses Trusted Execution Environments to build authenticity proofs of the external data [22]."
  ],
